column1: Documentation Required for EKS Cluster Version Upgrade
column20:
Current Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service) cluster version (1.21) has reached the end of its extended support period. To address this, it is imperative that we upgrade to a supported EKS version as soon as possible.

Could you please provide detailed documentation on the process to upgrade our EKS cluster version? Additionally, please specify the target version to which we should upgrade to ensure we are within a supported version range.

column1: Upyog Bootcamp Collections
column20:
I'm reaching out to you today with a pressing issue regarding our Upyog  Bootcamp collections. We've been trying extensively to resolve this problem, but we're still encountering errors in the Postman application.



I've attached relevant screenshots that demonstrate the errors we're facing. It's critical that we address this issue as soon as possible to ensure the smooth running of our bootcamp collections.

Please let me know the best way to proceed, and I'll make sure my team is available to work closely with you to get this resolved.



Thank you in advance for your prompt attention to this urgent matter.

column1: 1. Cesspool Operator Jurisdiction 2.  Contact Number
column20:
# Cesspool Operator Jurisdiction:

We are encountering a challenge with assigning the cesspool operator role across multiple jurisdictions. Specifically, we are attempting to assign a single cesspool operator to two distinct Urban Local Bodies (ULBs), namely:

* Kumhari- Nagar Palika (pg.Kumhari)
* Kumhari - Panchayat /Kumhari - Outside Boundary (pg.KumhariPanchayat)

Despite our efforts, the system restricts us from adding the same cesspool operator to both jurisdictions under the same contact number. For instance, the cesspool operator for Kumhari - Nagar Palika was successfully added with the contact number 9999999999. However, attempting to add this operator to Kumhari Panchayat with the same contact number results in a system rejection, although a different contact number seems to work. This limitation complicates our operations and we are keen on finding a viable solution. Are there any updates or workarounds that would allow us to assign multiple jurisdictions to a single cesspool operator?

We have provided the credentials below for your reference:

* ULB Operator: EMP-1013-000052/ eGov@4321

# Contact Number

When I am adding a contact number to Vehicle owner, and then the same to the driver, the system is not allowing me to add the details and throws the unhandled exception error. 
I tried the same after deleting the mobile number (vehicle contact number) mapped with the vehicle but still I am not able to add this mobile number to the vehicle.

column1: Manipur-Requesting Assistance in Frequency of Payment and fixation Assessment once a financial year
column20:
Hi ,

 As per the  Requirements of the Manipur Property Tax Rules

# There is a requirement Fixation of assessment once a year, where user can pay multiple time of the same assessment.
# User can have option of multiple frequency of payments (Half yearly / Quarterly/ Full) for the financial year while Assessment. Based on the mode selected there can provision for rebate which will be deducted from total amount calculated for assessment.

 Example

Assessment total calculated – Rs. 600

frequency of Payment selected – Quarterly.

Rebate = 10%

Assessment total calculated= 600 – 10% = 540

 For the above example assessment total will be 540/4 =  135 per quarter.

April -June = 135

July – September = 135

October – December = 135

January - March = 135

 Is there any existing process for the above requirement or need to be developed and  incorporate with existing application

 It would be great if our team and have a discussion related to this part of the calculator.

column1: UNICEF-Request for Guidance on features implementation approach - Web Page Creation, and FSTP Quality Testing.
column20:
As per the discussions during the meeting yesterday please find below the requirements:

# We would like to understand if there is a way to add a Web Page in the system where the users would be taken once they log in. 

For the beneficiaries (Citizens) the page would be having the details about the ULB with the contact details or any announcements added by the ULB. 

For the State Levels users we intend to embed a Dashboard, created on Google Data Studio or Power BI, into the webpage. This Dashboard would be just showing the details of the FSTP Status across all the ULBs. 

Kindly guide us how this can be achieved.

column1: UNICEF-FSM (Frontend Issue regarding to open the dashboard page)
column20:
Dear Sir, 

This is to confirm that we will be available for the meeting. We have updated the issue we are facing here: [https://github.com/orgs/upyog/discussions/729|https://github.com/orgs/upyog/discussions/729|smart-link] 

Copying the error here for your quick reference:

*Issue:-* when we open the FSM dashboard page then nothing happens Page redirects to the home page.
Nothing comes in the console and network tab.

*Approaches which we have taken:*-
We have tried the following things to solve the issue -
1:- As suggested by us we need to build the mono-ui for the dashboard so we have also built the same but still we can't able to open the dashboard.
2:- Then we also changed the Permission of the roles regarding the FSM dashboard and after this, we weren't able to solve the same.

column1: Uttarakhand -Issue in Finance & HRMS module
column20:
*Queries/Issues in Upyog/Digit Finance System*
*System Functionalities Related queries/concerns:*

* Expense Bill –
 Need to understand about the subledger details, how those subledger details
are coming in the form?
 Need to understand how Account code template is being created?
 How the sub ledger/secondary account code will come in net payable?
* Contractor/Supplier Bills –
 Need to understand, how Account code template is being created?
 Why contractor/Supplier name is not coming in net payable as the account
code.
* Contra Entries –
 Why Cash to Bank Transfer option is not there in the contra entries?
* Bank Reconciliation-
 All the modules under the Bank reconciliation needs to understand
functionality wise how it is working and when those will be used?
* Dishonour Cheque/DD-
 How dishonour cheque/DD information will be entered because there is no
option to enter the information that which cheque or DD is dishonoured.
* Sub-Ledger Configuration –
 Under the sub-ledger configuration there are two option sub ledger category
and sub ledger master but it is not clear that how subledgers are being
mapped with the chart of account.
* Miscellaneous Receipt –
 Where Service categories are defining and how the account codes are being
mapped with service categories.
* Budgeting –
 Need to understand whole budgeting process how it is being performed in
the system.
* Period End Activity –
 Need to understand whole period end activity process how it is being
performed in the system.
*Technical queries/concerns:*
* When we create the employee using HRMS, data saves in MDMS Json as
well as save in Tattva db. we just assign the approval role to the employee but
password is not there. when we create the user using the postman collection
it saves in the DB in the form of encrypted data. So, I need to understand the
whole process of the approval role in the application
* Token expire on local setup very frequently, how to manage it?
* Budget file download on local setup is not working.
* Revenue Collection is not working properly.
* In "View Remittance Bank Service Mapping" and "Remittance Collection
Report" only those account numbers are displaying in dropdown which are
mapped in MDMS by default rather than egcl_bankserviceaccountmapping
table. Why those account are coming from MDMS is there any specific
purpose?
* What is the significance of two different databases i.e. “tattva finance” and
"tattvadb" Which service is using which database and how those databases
are related to each other.

I wanted to address some issues related to our recently deployed application and discuss the necessary customization. Please find the details below:

# *UI Pointer Adjustment:*
Currently, our application is pointing to 'digit-ui', but we need to update it to 'upyog-ui'. To make this change, we'll need to adjust the relevant configuration settings or URL references in the codebase or configuration files. I encourage the development team to review these settings and ensure that the correct UI is being used.
# *Localization and Labeling:*
Some modules are not displaying the correct labels in the application. This could be a localization issue. I suggest that we review the code responsible for fetching and displaying labels to ensure that the appropriate resource files or database entries are being used based on the selected language or locale. Let's work together to identify and rectify this issue.
# *Changing Tenant:*
Our requirement includes changing the tenant. This involves customizing the application codebase to accommodate the new tenant's logic, database schema adjustments, and configuration settings. It's important that we carefully review the existing tenant-specific logic and make the necessary changes to accommodate the new tenant's requirements.

Let's collaborate closely to address these concerns and ensure that our application is functioning as intended. If you have any questions or suggestions, please feel free to share them.

column1: National Dashboard KPI issue.
column20:
We need clarification on the Following items regarding the National dashboard ingestAPIs:

# *In Property Tax Ingest API Payload*

{quote}"propertiesRegistered": [ { "groupBy": "financialYear", "buckets": [ { "name": "2018-19", "value": 12 }, { "name": "2019-20", "value": 18 }, { "name": "2020-21", "value": 21 } ] } ],{quote}

We are taking registered properties on the basis of financial years, does, State require to send this data every time in ingest request. As this data is historical/legacy data.

2.*In Trade License Ingest API payload,* there are two categories of data based on Status:

{quote}a) "todaysTradeLicenses": [ { "groupBy": "status", "buckets": [ { "name": "INITIATED", "value": 31 }, { "name": "APPLIED", "value": 56 }, { "name": "FIELDINSPECTION", "value": 32 }, { "name": "PENDINGAPPROVAL", "value": 44 }, { "name": "PENDINGPAYMENT", "value": 29 }, { "name": "APPROVED", "value": 23 }, { "name": "REJECTED", "value": 1 }, { "name": "EXPIRED", "value": 1 } ] } ],

and 

b) "applicationsMovedToday": [ { "groupBy": "status", "buckets": [ { "name": "INITIATED", "value": 31}, { "name": "APPLIED", "value": 56 }, { "name": "FIELDINSPECTION", "value": 32 }, { "name": "PENDINGAPPROVAL", "value": 44 }, { "name": "PENDINGPAYMENT", "value": 29 }, { "name": "APPROVED", "value": 23 }, { "name": "REJECTED", "value": 1 }, { "name": "EXPIRED", "value": 1 } ] } ]{quote}

Need to understand the basic difference between these two parameters. Can you please provide a basic description for the same.

3.*In Common Ingest API payload*, 

{quote}{ "date": "06-02-2022", "module": "COMMON", "ward": "Ward 1", "ulb": "pg.citya", "region": "CityA", "state": "PG","metrics": { "status": "Live", "onboardedUlbsCount": 12, "totalCitizensCount": 1250, "totalLiveUlbsCount": 15, "totalUlbCount": 22, "slaAchievement": 75, "liveUlbsCount": [ { "groupBy": "serviceModuleCode", "buckets": [ { "name": "PT", "value": 12 }, { "name": "TL", "value": 10 }, { "name": "FIRENOC", "value": 8 }, { "name": "PGR", "value": 22 }, { "name": "WS", "value": 12 } ] } ] } }{quote}

We are taking ward, ulb and region name and in the metrics, we are taking onboardedUlbsCount, totalLiveUlbsCount, totalUlbCount and liveUlbsCount group by serviceModuleCode. It is quite confusing that, if we are taking data for a state where we are taking total ulb count then, why are we saying state to put ward, ulb and region name. Please provide some clarity on this.

column1: CICD Deployment issue on SDC
column20:
Dear Team,

We are currently in the process of installing the DIGIT DevOps platform on our infrastructure and have encountered some challenges during the deployment.

 

*Current Stage:*

We have successfully configured the Jenkins Cluster using Kubespray, and we are now at the Jenkins deployment stage. We are following the DIGIT documentation for the production setup of the CI/CD pipeline, specifically the Jenkins deployment section: [https://core.digit.org/guides/installation-guide/production-setup/ci-cd-set-up#jenkins-deployment|https://core.digit.org/guides/installation-guide/production-setup/ci-cd-set-up#jenkins-deployment|smart-link] 

 

*Issues Faced:*

During the execution of the deployment command `go run main.go deploy -c -e ci 'jenkins,kaniko-cache-warmer,nginx-ingress,cert-manager'`, we encountered the following error:

 

*```*

error: resource mapping not found for name: "jenkins" namespace: "jenkins" from "jenkins/templates/jenkins-master-ingress.yaml": no matches for kind "Ingress" in version "[networking.k8s.io/v1beta1|http://networking.k8s.io/v1beta1]"

ensure CRDs are installed first

 

*```*



In response to the problem mentioned, we attempted to install Kubernetes version 1.2.0, but Kubespray no longer supports this version.

If we configure the cluster without using Kubespray, will it work? However, if there are particular guidelines or requirements we should adhere to, please inform us.



Thanks,

Joydeep

column1: OBPAS module - CCAVENUE Payment gateway
column20:
Our payment merchant redirect url is correctly generated and is working, but the url is not redirecting from our website to the  generated merchant url, its giving 405 Not allowed error on clicking the pay button. 

Our payment merchant url is - [https://test.ccavenue.com/transaction/transaction.do?command=initiateTransaction&&access_code=AVII96KA89BB16IIBB|https://test.ccavenue.com/transaction/transaction.do?command=initiateTransaction&&access_code=AVII96KA89BB16IIBB]



We are unable to find from which class the url is getting redirected.
